WEBVTT

00:09.096 --> 00:09.139
PENNYWORTH#107
"Julie Christie"
Closed Captioned

00:10.793 --> 00:11.750
Oh!

00:11.794 --> 00:14.057
My card.
Pennyworth Security.

00:14.101 --> 00:15.493
HARWOOD:
My name is Lord Harwood.

00:15.537 --> 00:17.713
We need men like you.

00:17.756 --> 00:18.757
ESME:
I don't know anything.

00:18.801 --> 00:19.758
Please don't hurt me.

00:22.718 --> 00:24.720
Who is the leader

00:24.763 --> 00:26.243
of the Raven Society?

00:26.287 --> 00:27.549
I'm the leader.

00:29.594 --> 00:31.248
SYKES:
It is you,

00:31.292 --> 00:33.076
isn't it?
Lord Harwood.

00:33.120 --> 00:35.078
What's going on?

00:35.122 --> 00:37.472
I know him.
He's me old boss.

00:37.515 --> 00:39.300
Oh, aye?

00:39.343 --> 00:42.303
So you want to call a truce?We do. Sincerely.

00:42.346 --> 00:46.611
That man tortured me.
He destroyed my life.

00:46.655 --> 00:48.265
H-He has to die.

00:48.309 --> 00:51.616
CURZON:
Do you really think
Esme died by accident?

00:51.660 --> 00:52.965
Who hates you

00:53.009 --> 00:55.272
so much that your death
isn't enough?

00:55.316 --> 00:59.146
What do you see?

00:59.189 --> 01:00.625
My God.

01:00.669 --> 01:02.366
He has been waiting all this
time to write me back.

01:02.410 --> 01:03.889
"A little too late, my friend.

01:03.933 --> 01:05.500
I'm glad you
know the truth."

01:05.543 --> 01:06.544
THOMAS:
Why is a nice American

01:06.588 --> 01:07.545
society girl like you mixed up

01:07.589 --> 01:08.720
with the No-Name League?

01:08.764 --> 01:10.200
I could ask the same of you.

01:10.244 --> 01:11.680
THOMAS:
This is my sister
Patricia.

01:11.723 --> 01:13.334
Could I leave her with
you for a few hours?

01:13.377 --> 01:15.945
PATRICIA:
Do you like parties, Martha?

01:15.988 --> 01:17.468
Who the hell isthis guy?

01:17.512 --> 01:19.383
PATRICIA:
Alistair is a Satanist.

01:19.427 --> 01:20.471
Oh, I love her already.

01:40.187 --> 01:42.928
♪ Well, you've got
your diamonds ♪

01:42.972 --> 01:47.281
♪ And you've got
your pretty clothes ♪

01:47.324 --> 01:51.198
♪ And the chauffeur drives
your car ♪

01:51.241 --> 01:55.680
♪ You let everybody know

01:55.724 --> 01:59.510
♪ But don't play with me

01:59.554 --> 02:01.817
♪ 'Cause you're playing
with fire ♪

02:03.949 --> 02:07.736
♪ So, don't you play with me

02:07.779 --> 02:10.739
♪ 'Cause you're playing
with fire. ♪

02:10.782 --> 02:11.740
THOMAS: Thank God!

02:11.783 --> 02:13.698
Where have you been?

02:13.742 --> 02:15.135
What the hell?
Where's Patricia?

02:15.178 --> 02:16.223
What-- where are
your clothes?

02:19.400 --> 02:20.357
Jesus, are you okay?

02:20.401 --> 02:21.402
What the hell happened to you?

02:21.445 --> 02:24.144
I'm fine.

02:24.187 --> 02:26.624
Calm down.

02:26.668 --> 02:27.625
What are you doing

02:27.669 --> 02:29.061
in my apartment?

02:29.105 --> 02:31.934
Calm down?
I thought you were dead.

02:31.977 --> 02:33.065
I've been worried sick.

02:36.417 --> 02:39.811
We went out to a party, and I
guess things got a little wild.

02:39.855 --> 02:41.813
Got a little wild?
You are naked!

02:41.857 --> 02:43.511
Where is Patricia?

02:43.554 --> 02:47.036
Patricia is a lunatic,
but she's a grown woman.

02:47.079 --> 02:49.778
I'm not her nanny,
and you're not her father,

02:49.821 --> 02:52.520
and anyway, what was I
supposed to do?

02:52.563 --> 02:54.391
I'm sure Patricia's just...

02:54.435 --> 02:56.828
sleeping it off
someplace.

02:56.872 --> 02:58.917
Oh, unbelievable.
The irresponsibility!

02:58.961 --> 03:01.529
Please.

03:01.572 --> 03:04.053
Like you never got drunk
and lost track of time.

03:04.096 --> 03:06.360
You have been gone
for three days!

03:06.403 --> 03:08.013
Three days? What are
you talking about?

03:08.057 --> 03:10.233
Today's Saturday.Martha, it's Monday.

03:10.277 --> 03:11.800
No.
Monday!

03:16.413 --> 03:19.024
What the fuck?

03:19.068 --> 03:21.157
What the hell
happened to you?

03:21.201 --> 03:22.593
Where is Patricia?

04:43.892 --> 04:44.849
Anything?

04:44.893 --> 04:46.416
Nothing.Daveboy?

04:46.460 --> 04:48.375
Nope, nothing, Alfie, sorry.

04:51.073 --> 04:52.509
There's got to be something.
Tell us where he's hiding.

04:59.777 --> 05:00.691
Alfie?

05:05.348 --> 05:07.045
What is it?

05:24.193 --> 05:25.803
The bastard wore it
like a medal.

05:27.196 --> 05:29.111
I don't understand.

05:30.242 --> 05:32.157
All you done
was make a joke.

05:35.639 --> 05:38.120
It was just a joke.

05:43.691 --> 05:45.736
Laugh's on me, eh?

05:49.827 --> 05:51.307
The witch was right.

05:55.920 --> 05:58.140
It's my fault Esme's dead.

06:00.925 --> 06:02.840
And now he's playing with me.

06:05.582 --> 06:08.977
He's the cat.
And I'm the mouse.

06:10.805 --> 06:13.634
BAZZA:
Alfie?

06:13.677 --> 06:16.550
Look around you.

06:16.593 --> 06:17.507
The man's crazy.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.555
There's no reason
in crazy.

06:39.094 --> 06:40.617
I don't even know
his first name.

06:40.661 --> 06:42.184
I just clean his
house. That's all.

06:42.227 --> 06:44.708
Mondays and Thursdays.

06:44.752 --> 06:46.101
You're not a very
good cleaner.

06:46.144 --> 06:49.844
Mr. Curzon is
very particular.

06:49.887 --> 06:52.194
Uh, he only has me
clean his quarters.

06:52.237 --> 06:53.674
I'm not to touch the
rest of the house.

06:53.717 --> 06:54.892
What sort of a man is he?

06:54.936 --> 06:57.373
Oh, like any other man,
I suppose.

06:57.417 --> 06:59.201
Well, does he have a job,
friends, family?

06:59.244 --> 07:01.856
I do Mondays and Thursdays.

07:01.899 --> 07:02.857
Have you any idea
where he's gone?

07:04.511 --> 07:06.469
What did he do?

07:06.513 --> 07:08.950
Did he ever talk
of an Alfred Pennyworth?

07:08.993 --> 07:11.474
Like I said, we
don't speak much.

07:11.518 --> 07:12.693
He's up at the crack,

07:12.736 --> 07:14.129
puts on his uniform,
and off he goes.

07:14.172 --> 07:15.347
Uniform?

07:15.391 --> 07:17.262
He's still
commissioned?

07:17.306 --> 07:19.090
Not according
to the Records Office, he's not.

07:19.134 --> 07:24.835
So where the fuck is he going
all dolled up?

07:28.578 --> 07:31.407
SYKES:
Please let me come.

07:31.451 --> 07:32.626
You know it's not down to me.

07:32.669 --> 07:33.757
I wouldn't leave you
on your own.

07:33.801 --> 07:36.064
It's Lord Snooty's decree.

07:36.107 --> 07:38.022
Be fair, Peg. You
know it makes sense.

07:38.066 --> 07:39.807
She's a liability.

07:39.850 --> 07:41.635
A liability?

07:41.678 --> 07:43.201
All I
mean to say is

07:43.245 --> 07:45.639
that someone might
recognize you, my dove,

07:45.682 --> 07:48.293
that's all.I know what
liability means.

07:48.337 --> 07:51.427
Off you go.
Don't mind me.

07:51.471 --> 07:52.994
We won't be long, will we?

07:53.037 --> 07:56.214
No. Sorry, Bet.

07:56.258 --> 07:58.521
Come now.
Wish us luck.

08:01.611 --> 08:02.743
Luck.

08:53.315 --> 08:54.359
Good morning.

08:57.449 --> 08:59.408
We're here to see Dr. Gaunt.

08:59.451 --> 09:02.846
Surgery hours are
between 12:00 and 6:00.

09:02.890 --> 09:06.023
Nobody's poorly, love.
It's a social call.

09:06.067 --> 09:07.068
There's nobody listed.

09:07.111 --> 09:09.984
It's a surprise visit.

09:10.027 --> 09:11.986
If you're not
on the list...

09:12.029 --> 09:13.944
you're not on the list.

09:13.988 --> 09:15.511
She'll want to see us.

09:37.664 --> 09:39.622
Good morning, madam.
How can I help?

09:39.666 --> 09:40.884
If you've come
to sell something,

09:40.928 --> 09:42.973
the answer is:
no, thank you, good day.

09:43.017 --> 09:44.975
PEGGY:
Alone, are we?

09:45.019 --> 09:47.499
Now that's
an impertinent question.

09:47.543 --> 09:48.849
Why do you ask?

09:48.892 --> 09:51.460
We've a situation
wanting discretion.

09:51.503 --> 09:54.115
Loose lips sink
ships and all that.

09:54.158 --> 09:55.507
I'm listening.

09:55.551 --> 09:57.205
So you're alone, then?Yes, I am.

09:57.248 --> 09:58.728
Explain yourself, madam.

10:07.128 --> 10:09.260
My God, James!

10:09.304 --> 10:11.219
Hello, Frances.

10:11.262 --> 10:14.004
I thought you were dead!
We all thought you were dead.

10:14.048 --> 10:18.356
Well, I rather thought so, too,
but, um... well, here I am.

10:18.400 --> 10:19.575
Oh...

10:20.707 --> 10:23.144
Oh.

10:32.153 --> 10:34.634
MARTHA:
This is the place.

10:34.677 --> 10:36.200
THOMAS:
You sure?

10:36.244 --> 10:37.898
I mean, it looks
different in daylight,

10:37.941 --> 10:41.336
but... yeah, I'm pretty sure.

10:41.379 --> 10:43.077
This is the place, I think.You think?

10:43.120 --> 10:44.513
Would you please stop
repeating everything

10:44.556 --> 10:46.167
I say in a loud voice?

10:46.210 --> 10:49.561
I can't believe I trusted you.
What a mess.

10:49.605 --> 10:51.259
It's all I need
right now.

10:51.302 --> 10:53.435
Then go. I can handle this.

10:53.478 --> 10:54.436
Three days, Martha.

10:54.479 --> 10:56.960
A three-day blackout?

10:57.004 --> 10:59.528
Forgive me if I doubt
your ability to handle this.

10:59.571 --> 11:01.399
I can and I will.

11:01.443 --> 11:03.619
You have no conception of
the trouble you've caused.

11:03.663 --> 11:04.794
Every time Patricia
pulls this sort of crap,

11:04.838 --> 11:06.361
it ends up in
the papers,

11:06.404 --> 11:07.710
and the Wayne family name
gets dragged through the mud.

11:07.754 --> 11:10.104
You self-important boob.

11:10.147 --> 11:13.107
I woke up naked
on Hampstead Heath.

11:13.150 --> 11:14.586
I have no idea
what happened to me.

11:14.630 --> 11:16.632
Your sister
is missing and...

11:16.676 --> 11:18.025
you're worried
about your name?

11:21.985 --> 11:25.380
Oh... hello.

11:32.909 --> 11:34.345
Welcome back, Martha.

11:35.999 --> 11:37.392
Who's your friend?

11:37.435 --> 11:40.787
Pardon the intrusion.

11:40.830 --> 11:44.442
This young lady says
that my sister might be here.

11:44.486 --> 11:45.792
Patricia Wayne.

11:45.835 --> 11:47.532
We've always got so many guests.

11:51.188 --> 11:53.103
Where's Crowley?

11:53.147 --> 11:54.757
I want to speak to him.

11:54.801 --> 11:56.759
Immediately.

11:56.803 --> 11:59.893
Have a drink.
Wet your whistle.

11:59.936 --> 12:02.156
I'm sure we have
anything you'd like.

12:02.199 --> 12:03.766
No, thank you.

12:03.810 --> 12:05.202
As I was saying,
my sister?

12:05.246 --> 12:06.682
Where's Crowley?

12:06.726 --> 12:09.554
Hold your horses, Martha.
He'll be along.

12:09.598 --> 12:12.035
Call me Miss Kane,
whoever the hell you are.

12:12.079 --> 12:13.558
Whoare you?

12:13.602 --> 12:16.910
Oh. I'm sorry,

12:16.953 --> 12:20.000
I... I thought
you'd remember me.

12:21.175 --> 12:22.437
Such fun we had.

12:25.919 --> 12:28.617
If I don't see Crowley
and Patricia Wayne down here

12:28.660 --> 12:30.880
right this minute,
I'm calling the police.

12:30.924 --> 12:33.578
Oh, no, no, no.
No, don't do that.

12:33.622 --> 12:36.364
No police.No.

12:36.407 --> 12:38.670
We don't want
the police here, either.

12:38.714 --> 12:39.759
We just want my sister.

12:41.543 --> 12:42.674
Miss Kane.

12:42.718 --> 12:45.634
How lovely to
see you again.

12:45.677 --> 12:47.027
And in such

12:47.070 --> 12:48.506
illustrious company.

12:49.681 --> 12:51.901
The famous
Thomas Wayne.

12:51.945 --> 12:53.729
Your sister speaks
very highly of you.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.557
I doubt that.

12:55.600 --> 12:57.515
Crowley, is it?

12:58.690 --> 13:00.692
Where is my sister?I'm so sorry

13:00.736 --> 13:01.737
you've been
worried about her.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.217
Patricia's fine.

13:03.260 --> 13:05.654
She's upstairs.
Safe and sound.

13:05.697 --> 13:10.920
Well... good.
Bring her here, please.

13:10.964 --> 13:12.356
Of course.

13:12.400 --> 13:15.272
My angel, fetch
Patricia, would you?

13:17.927 --> 13:20.190
Thank you.

13:20.234 --> 13:23.846
If she is indeed okay,
you have my apologies

13:23.890 --> 13:24.934
for coming in

13:24.978 --> 13:26.457
hot, so to speak.Apology, my ass.

13:26.501 --> 13:29.243
I'm missing three days
of my life

13:29.286 --> 13:31.549
thanks to whatever it is
you slipped into my drink.

13:31.593 --> 13:33.595
Three days?

13:33.638 --> 13:35.597
Dear me.

13:35.640 --> 13:39.340
Mmm. I can assure you, Martha,

13:39.383 --> 13:41.168
I slipped nothing
into your drink.

13:41.211 --> 13:43.170
Perhaps the police
can find out.

13:43.213 --> 13:46.303
Martha, I'm sorry
you didn't have a good time.

13:46.347 --> 13:48.305
I haven't the foggiest notion
what happened to you.

13:48.349 --> 13:50.220
I'm afraid I wasn't
paying attention.

13:50.264 --> 13:51.918
It was a good party.

13:51.961 --> 13:53.267
And I rather took you
for an adult.

13:53.310 --> 13:57.314
As for the police,
call them, by all means.

13:57.358 --> 13:59.012
The chief inspector
is a dear friend.

13:59.055 --> 14:00.970
He'll tell you I'm a good egg.

14:01.014 --> 14:02.711
A good egg?

14:02.754 --> 14:03.930
Martha.

14:03.973 --> 14:06.497
Let's not make
a federal case of this.

14:06.541 --> 14:09.413
If Patricia is okay, there's
no need to involve the police.

14:09.457 --> 14:12.068
I'll be the judge of that.

14:12.112 --> 14:14.114
Where's the crime here?

14:14.157 --> 14:16.551
Sin we have in joyful abundance,

14:16.594 --> 14:18.205
but crime... no.

14:26.953 --> 14:29.085
There was a man
with a goat's head.

14:31.783 --> 14:33.350
There was blood.
I remember that much.

14:33.394 --> 14:35.222
Dear me.

14:35.265 --> 14:36.484
You did have a wild old time.

14:36.527 --> 14:38.442
A goat's head forsooth.

14:38.486 --> 14:40.662
Martha, I...Don't "Martha" me.

14:42.969 --> 14:45.797
Tommy.

14:45.841 --> 14:47.974
Oh, my goodness.
Patricia.

14:48.017 --> 14:50.759
Are you,
are you okay?

14:50.802 --> 14:52.413
You are so cute.

14:52.456 --> 14:54.023
You mean, was I ravished

14:54.067 --> 14:56.112
by the devil?
Violated

14:56.156 --> 14:58.071
by Beelzebub?

14:58.114 --> 15:00.900
Okay. Get your things.
We're leaving.

15:00.943 --> 15:03.946
Leaving? Oh, no,
I'm not leaving.

15:03.990 --> 15:05.382
I'm finally home.

15:05.426 --> 15:07.732
Don't be ridiculous.
This isn't your home.

15:07.776 --> 15:10.474
And this man--
I don't know who this man is

15:10.518 --> 15:13.260
but he's not respectable
and you're not staying here.

15:13.303 --> 15:15.262
Mr. Wayne.

15:15.305 --> 15:17.046
Patricia is an adult.

15:17.090 --> 15:18.787
If she wishes to stay,

15:18.830 --> 15:20.267
what kind of host
would I be

15:20.310 --> 15:22.356
to let her be taken
against her will?

15:22.399 --> 15:25.794
Patricia...
I would like to speak

15:25.837 --> 15:27.752
with you... alone.Don't want to.

15:27.796 --> 15:29.841
CROWLEY:
Go along and be nice,

15:29.885 --> 15:31.408
Patricia.

15:31.452 --> 15:32.757
Talk to him.

15:32.801 --> 15:35.325
He's family.

15:46.162 --> 15:47.903
Do you have...

15:47.947 --> 15:50.166
Mrs. Bung,
the brewer's wife?

16:00.046 --> 16:02.178
GAUNT:
We were rather lost

16:02.222 --> 16:03.701
without your
leadership.

16:03.745 --> 16:06.530
You are a
species of a miracle.

16:06.574 --> 16:08.924
I am, aren't I?

16:08.968 --> 16:12.623
A battered...
somewhat grotesque miracle.

16:12.667 --> 16:14.364
My gosh.

16:14.408 --> 16:17.019
What horrors you have suffered.
We must

16:17.063 --> 16:19.021
get you out
of the country

16:19.065 --> 16:20.980
and beyond our
enemies' reach.

16:21.023 --> 16:22.242
The Germans...

16:22.285 --> 16:24.244
would be glad to offer refuge.

16:24.287 --> 16:27.029
Oh, heavens no.
I can't leave England.

16:27.073 --> 16:29.118
The crisis is coming.

16:29.162 --> 16:30.728
The game's afoot.

16:30.772 --> 16:33.775
Well, I... defer
to your judgment of course,

16:33.818 --> 16:37.561
but... I-I rather think
the peace that we've...

16:37.605 --> 16:40.129
cobbled together--
will hold.

16:40.173 --> 16:42.088
I hope so.

16:42.131 --> 16:43.611
Peace...

16:43.654 --> 16:46.179
above all things.Absolutely.

16:46.222 --> 16:48.181
But Undine Thwaite is no fool.

16:48.224 --> 16:50.357
She'll break the truce...

16:50.400 --> 16:51.836
as soon as
she's consolidated power.

16:51.880 --> 16:54.317
You think so?

16:54.361 --> 16:58.147
Mrs. Thwaite seems sincere

16:58.191 --> 17:00.236
in her desire for peace.You had

17:00.280 --> 17:02.151
her husband killed
in front of her.

17:02.195 --> 17:03.674
Bold and ruthless move,

17:03.718 --> 17:05.937
by the way.
Brava.

17:05.981 --> 17:07.722
But...

17:07.765 --> 17:09.898
I expect she'd be
rather vengeful.

17:09.941 --> 17:11.117
Whatever she may say.

17:11.160 --> 17:14.076
I did not kill Julian Thwaite.

17:15.730 --> 17:18.428
Everyone, ev-everyone thinks
I did, but I didn't.

17:18.472 --> 17:20.343
Interesting.

17:23.216 --> 17:25.392
This murderous sort
of political intrigue

17:25.435 --> 17:27.394
is beyond my ken.

17:27.437 --> 17:29.396
Now, tell me your
plans, I am at

17:29.439 --> 17:30.658
your disposal.

17:30.701 --> 17:32.877
My plan is simple.

17:32.921 --> 17:34.749
Redemption.

17:34.792 --> 17:36.490
A glorious triumph.

17:36.533 --> 17:38.448
A national awakening.

17:40.015 --> 17:41.712
I will destroy my enemies

17:41.756 --> 17:44.106
and lead this country
back to greatness.

17:44.150 --> 17:46.326
Okay.

17:46.369 --> 17:48.328
Touch ambitious, maybe.

17:48.371 --> 17:50.025
How are you going
to do that, exactly?

17:50.069 --> 17:51.940
I mean, if you
reveal yourself,

17:51.983 --> 17:53.333
the government
will arrest you

17:53.376 --> 17:55.335
and they will not
make the mistake

17:55.378 --> 17:57.293
of letting you live this time.Yes.

17:59.165 --> 18:00.688
For now...

18:00.731 --> 18:02.124
I shall remain in hiding.

18:02.168 --> 18:04.909
We will let the Raven Society

18:04.953 --> 18:06.955
grand council know
that I'm alive and well,

18:06.998 --> 18:08.261
but no one else must know.

18:08.304 --> 18:10.350
And then...

18:10.393 --> 18:11.655
when the time is right,

18:11.699 --> 18:13.918
I shall reveal myself publicly.

18:13.962 --> 18:15.442
To maximum effect.

18:15.485 --> 18:17.531
I see.

18:23.363 --> 18:24.929
You seem doubtful.

18:24.973 --> 18:26.583
No, no, no, no, no.

18:26.627 --> 18:28.846
